== Introduction ==

A way to organize your media files based on the different containers the audio and video codecs and the subtitle formats

== Usage example ==
=== Mounting your media directory ===
{{{
dmxfs ~/media/ ~/dmxfs
}}}

=== Listing all the caps of your media files ===
{{{
#> ls -l ~/dmxfs
drwxr-xr-x 2 root root 0 1970-01-01 01:00 application_ogg
drwxr-xr-x 2 root root 0 1970-01-01 01:00 application_vnd.rn-realmedia
drwxr-xr-x 2 root root 0 1970-01-01 01:00 application_x-apetag
drwxr-xr-x 2 root root 0 1970-01-01 01:00 application_x-id3
drwxr-xr-x 2 root root 0 1970-01-01 01:00 application_x-rar
drwxr-xr-x 2 root root 0 1970-01-01 01:00 audio_midi
drwxr-xr-x 2 root root 0 1970-01-01 01:00 audio_mpeg
drwxr-xr-x 2 root root 0 1970-01-01 01:00 audio_x-ac3
drwxr-xr-x 2 root root 0 1970-01-01 01:00 audio_x-dts
drwxr-xr-x 2 root root 0 1970-01-01 01:00 audio_x-flac
